-- Pearson says not pursuing Dow Jones tie-up
-- 
-- Thu Jun 21, 2007 12:29pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/21/us-pearson-dowjones-idUSWLA046520070621

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Pearson ( PSON.L ), the world's largest educational publisher, said on Thursday it had decided not to pursue a bid for Dow Jones DJ.N with General Electric ( GE.N ). 

 Pearson, which publishes the Financial Times, said it remained in talks with General Electric, which controls the CNBC cable business channel, about co-operation agreements.